WEBVTT

00:51.468 --> 00:53.011
EPISODE 1

00:53.136 --> 00:54.888
You're not allowed to use

00:54.971 --> 00:57.140
or even have your phone
on you during your shift.

00:57.223 --> 00:59.267
Please put it in your locker right away.

01:04.272 --> 01:06.149
Why is it so dusty here?

01:12.739 --> 01:16.576
I think you trust the fridge too much.

01:17.577 --> 01:20.080
Ingredients can go bad
even when they are frozen.

01:20.330 --> 01:23.124
Please throw out
all the expired ingredients.

01:23.208 --> 01:24.083
Yes, ma'am.

01:30.757 --> 01:32.759
Wipe this again and organize everything.

01:34.302 --> 01:37.263
Please clean where I left notes on.

01:45.021 --> 01:48.066
I'm a woman too, so I totally understand

01:48.149 --> 01:50.026
that you want to look taller and slimmer.

01:50.193 --> 01:53.404
But heels can be dangerous
because the floor is slippery.

01:57.575 --> 01:59.577
It's for your safety,

01:59.911 --> 02:01.913
so don't get annoyed, okay?

02:03.665 --> 02:05.542
MY BOYFRIEND

02:05.792 --> 02:07.836
Can we meet today?
I have something to tell you.

02:10.713 --> 02:13.383
Gyeong-seon, did you read my mind or what?

02:13.508 --> 02:15.343
I was just about to call you.

02:15.969 --> 02:18.179
Why? Do you miss me?

02:20.014 --> 02:22.350
Gyu-min wants to see me today.

02:22.809 --> 02:25.311
What did he sound like?
Are you getting a bad feeling?

02:27.564 --> 02:28.690
I am indeed.

02:28.773 --> 02:31.192
Hey, do not look insecure, okay?

02:31.776 --> 02:33.319
You know what I mean, right?

02:34.404 --> 02:35.530
Of course.

02:51.546 --> 02:54.507
- Could you send this to my home address?
- Sure.

02:55.508 --> 02:57.302
Do you have a pair of stockings on hand?

02:57.385 --> 03:00.805
Yes, I'll give it to you.
How would you like to pay for this?

03:01.681 --> 03:04.434
- What's my total again?
- It's 327,000 won.

03:04.517 --> 03:05.560
Then...

03:09.564 --> 03:12.108
In three monthly installments, please.
There's no interest, right?

03:19.532 --> 03:21.242
And this place too.

03:22.118 --> 03:26.164
They have all-you-can-eat sashimi,
but I heard the fish is very fresh.

03:26.497 --> 03:29.751
They get oysters directly from the source,
so they taste amazing during the season.

03:29.876 --> 03:32.045
Look at this. Doesn't it look so good?

03:32.712 --> 03:34.422
You love oysters.

03:34.505 --> 03:36.591
We'll definitely get
our money's worth here, right?

03:43.514 --> 03:46.559
This Valentine's Day is
our first anniversary, you know.

03:46.643 --> 03:47.685
Let's go to Namhae County.

03:48.144 --> 03:50.271
There's an amazing resort with a pool,

03:50.355 --> 03:52.523
and it's run
by one of my clients' relative.

03:52.607 --> 03:56.027
You have to book a month before,
but they'll make an exception for me.

03:56.152 --> 03:57.028
Look at this.

03:57.695 --> 04:00.907
Isn't this place awesome?
It's so luxurious.

04:13.920 --> 04:15.380
Why don't you love me anymore?

04:19.133 --> 04:21.511
- It's not that.
- Then why break up?

04:24.305 --> 04:27.267
That's why you wanted to see me today.
Aren't I right?

04:31.312 --> 04:32.230
Lee Gyu-min.

04:33.690 --> 04:34.941
Are you seeing someone else?

04:37.568 --> 04:38.778
Then what is it?

04:39.862 --> 04:41.406
There must be a reason.

04:41.698 --> 04:42.573
What is it?

04:43.449 --> 04:45.994
Am I not hot enough?
Does my fashion sense suck?

04:47.578 --> 04:49.080
Is it because our personalities clash?

04:49.872 --> 04:51.541
Because my dad isn't rich?

04:51.833 --> 04:54.127
What else could it be?
Because I'm not in my 20s?

04:54.210 --> 04:56.170
Whatever it is,
I'm sure there is a reason.

04:57.130 --> 04:58.131
If that's not the case...

04:59.924 --> 05:00.925
I'll be blunt.

05:02.427 --> 05:03.594
Because we've done it all?

05:04.804 --> 05:06.764
- Jin-a.
- What is it then?

05:06.848 --> 05:09.225
Give me a reason so that I can accept it.

05:17.817 --> 05:19.360
Our relationship is...

05:22.822 --> 05:23.948
not exciting anymore.

05:24.449 --> 05:25.950
You might not understand what I mean.

05:27.577 --> 05:29.871
Right, I don't.

05:30.830 --> 05:31.998
In other words...

05:34.375 --> 05:35.418
You know.

05:37.336 --> 05:38.421
It's like konjac.

05:41.924 --> 05:42.842
Konjac?

05:55.146 --> 05:56.064
So...

06:00.401 --> 06:02.695
Basically, you are saying

06:02.987 --> 06:05.573
that you expect nothing from me anymore.

06:05.656 --> 06:07.742
I said it's about us.
You are overreacting.

06:09.368 --> 06:12.288
It’s not you.
I'm talking about our relationship.

06:13.414 --> 06:15.291
You are playing with words

06:16.709 --> 06:19.962
so that you can pretend that you’re not
like other men. Am I wrong?

06:21.881 --> 06:24.926
Let's stop. I can't get through to you.

06:36.979 --> 06:38.564
Come on, I'll give you a ride.

06:43.653 --> 06:44.779
Fine, then.

06:46.489 --> 06:47.406
Take care.

07:02.421 --> 07:03.464
Jin-a.

07:08.469 --> 07:11.264
I have to pay for the valet,
but I don't have any cash on me right now.

07:11.347 --> 07:12.348
Do you happen to have...

07:18.438 --> 07:20.022
Hold on. I'll give you the change.

07:20.106 --> 07:21.149
Forget it.

07:21.607 --> 07:24.318
Now that I'll be gone, you should
pick up the habit of carrying cash.

08:43.814 --> 08:45.566
Call me immediately after you see this

08:45.650 --> 08:46.943
or else.

08:50.780 --> 08:51.948
Moron.

08:54.408 --> 08:56.827
I told you not to let him get to you,
did you forget?

08:57.119 --> 08:59.413
What did you buy a new dress for?

09:01.624 --> 09:03.084
Are you made of money?

09:07.797 --> 09:09.131
Stop scolding me.

09:10.675 --> 09:15.388
I looked up konjac
to see what he meant by that.

09:16.472 --> 09:17.765
Did you have to look it up?

09:18.432 --> 09:21.477
It's right here. Nobody likes it.

09:21.811 --> 09:25.439
It tastes like nothing,
and something's not right about it.

09:26.899 --> 09:29.944
Hey! Why is everything my fault?

09:30.987 --> 09:34.991
He didn't bring anything new to the table.

09:35.992 --> 09:39.704
I was at the top of my game
until a few years ago.

09:40.496 --> 09:41.539
You know what?

09:42.748 --> 09:46.502
My first love, Jun-u,
called and said he missed me.

09:46.627 --> 09:48.421
Here you go again.

09:48.546 --> 09:50.673
Don't you remember that?

09:50.923 --> 09:54.885
- What?
- I told you about that college student...

09:54.969 --> 09:57.054
Are you bringing that up again?

09:58.014 --> 10:01.892
He waited for me in front of my house
to get my number.

10:01.976 --> 10:04.437
I was 31 back then.

10:05.563 --> 10:07.148
Good for you.

10:07.481 --> 10:09.442
How are you different from those

10:09.525 --> 10:12.903
who can't seem to let go of
their good old days?

10:13.904 --> 10:16.282
He asked for a breakup,
and you just accepted it.

10:16.407 --> 10:17.867
Is that really the best you could do?

10:18.451 --> 10:21.495
I would have slapped him
across the face at the word konjac.

10:23.998 --> 10:25.499
Gosh.

10:27.209 --> 10:31.088
I had so much going for me
in the old days.

10:32.089 --> 10:33.633
Am I...

10:34.091 --> 10:35.176
Am I that bad?

10:35.259 --> 10:38.012
Tell me. Am I really that unattractive?

10:39.055 --> 10:41.682
Being horribly unattractive
could be a unique trait.

10:42.183 --> 10:45.603
You are more like... Right, you are bland.

10:46.187 --> 10:47.563
Do you call yourself a friend?

10:47.647 --> 10:49.440
But there's no difference. Why?

10:49.523 --> 10:52.526
Most men's ideal type of woman

10:52.610 --> 10:53.944
is this.

10:54.320 --> 10:56.155
The new young girl.

10:59.450 --> 11:01.077
This isn't the first time you got dumped.

11:04.163 --> 11:05.373
I'm telling you.

11:06.290 --> 11:08.501
You should raise your standards

11:09.043 --> 11:10.628
or do something about it.

11:13.714 --> 11:15.424
I want tteokbokki.

11:16.759 --> 11:18.052
Let's go get some tteokbokki.

11:18.594 --> 11:20.971
- I want to go do karaoke too.
- I'm in.

11:22.306 --> 11:23.474
I'm going to sing.

11:23.557 --> 11:26.977
- Just one more song.
- You've sung enough.

11:27.061 --> 11:29.730
No, hold on. Come here.

11:29.939 --> 11:33.150
Let's talk outside. Be careful.

11:33.234 --> 11:35.611
Let's just sing one more song.

11:35.820 --> 11:37.363
- Ouch.
- Come on.

11:38.280 --> 11:39.281
Hey.

11:40.699 --> 11:43.536
- Singing is not going to bring him back.
- Just one.

11:43.619 --> 11:46.664
Even if it does, you shouldn't accept him.

11:46.747 --> 11:48.082
Hey, I'm...

11:48.958 --> 11:51.335
I'm singing for myself.

11:51.919 --> 11:54.964
I feel so depressed.

11:56.048 --> 11:57.174
On days

11:57.758 --> 12:02.221
When everything makes you blue

12:02.304 --> 12:05.933
Sing this song

12:06.350 --> 12:12.273
You still have fire in your heart

12:12.356 --> 12:15.109
Fight until the end
And don't let them get to you

12:22.408 --> 12:25.661
Throw all your regrets

12:25.744 --> 12:27.663
Into the sky

12:29.290 --> 12:30.958
My friend

12:31.041 --> 12:34.003
Let's start over

12:34.086 --> 12:35.963
Disheartened life

12:36.046 --> 12:39.800
Doesn't suit you

12:40.259 --> 12:43.971
Keep your head held high, my friend

12:44.054 --> 12:46.765
Now is the beginning

12:49.393 --> 12:53.856
Throw all your regrets into the sky

14:04.468 --> 14:06.303
I'm sorry.

14:08.597 --> 14:10.349
I'm sorry.

14:26.240 --> 14:27.825
My gosh.

15:29.595 --> 15:32.264
Why don't you just live here
if you're going to drop by all the time?

15:33.140 --> 15:35.601
There isn't an alcoholic
who disturbs me in my dorm room.

15:35.684 --> 15:36.852
It's better there.

15:37.895 --> 15:39.772
Take it easy on the alcohol.
Think of your age.

15:39.855 --> 15:40.689
Do you want to die?

15:40.773 --> 15:42.483
- What?
- Stop bothering him.

15:42.691 --> 15:43.692
Aren't you his big sister?

15:44.443 --> 15:46.946
You said it was too bitter,
so I added some licorice this time

15:47.029 --> 15:47.988
to make it sweeter.

15:48.197 --> 15:50.366
Don't leave it out for too long,
and drink it like water.

15:50.866 --> 15:53.035
Call me if you need some more.

15:53.118 --> 15:56.205
Same with any dishes.
I can always drive to Daejeon.

15:56.455 --> 15:58.874
I think your dad is washing up.

15:59.124 --> 16:01.418
Seung-ho's leaving!
You're late. You should go.

16:01.919 --> 16:06.507
Seung-ho, drive safely.
Text me as soon as you arrive.

16:06.590 --> 16:08.926
- If you need anything--
- I got it.

16:09.134 --> 16:11.512
- Seung-ho, drive safely.
- All right.

16:11.595 --> 16:14.932
Don't skip any meals, all right?
Make sure you--

16:16.141 --> 16:19.103
Call me if you need anything, okay?

16:25.275 --> 16:27.653
You should have brought
a telephone pole home with you.

16:28.570 --> 16:29.613
I won't do it again.

16:30.239 --> 16:34.368
Gyu-min, that punk.
Why would he make you drink so much?

16:35.369 --> 16:38.205
We were good to him
and now, he's disrespecting us.

16:38.539 --> 16:40.082
Tell him to come over this weekend.

16:40.290 --> 16:41.542
I'm going to scold him.

16:42.376 --> 16:43.919
Why aren't you answering me?

16:45.379 --> 16:46.380
Okay.

16:47.423 --> 16:51.093
I have to make hangover soup
every other day. I'm sick of it.

16:51.343 --> 16:53.345
- Grab a spoon and sit.
- I'm late.

16:54.179 --> 16:56.890
I made it for you!
Who's going to eat this now?

17:02.312 --> 17:04.565
You sure have luck on your side.

17:16.618 --> 17:17.453
Come in.

17:19.163 --> 17:20.164
Are you late?

17:20.539 --> 17:22.041
I might just make it.

17:22.124 --> 17:24.626
If I run to the station,
I might make it on time.

17:24.835 --> 17:26.211
Should I drive you to work?

17:28.047 --> 17:29.048
Well...

17:30.257 --> 17:32.760
We should make good use of my retirement.

17:33.927 --> 17:38.265
That's true. It's okay, though.
You can drive me next time.

17:39.266 --> 17:40.267
See you later.

17:41.518 --> 17:43.562
- Be careful.
- Okay.

20:22.429 --> 20:23.388
You punk!

20:32.231 --> 20:33.273
Jun-hui.

20:34.274 --> 20:35.400
Welcome back.

20:41.448 --> 20:42.449
You little punk!

20:43.784 --> 20:45.410
Let's end this here.

20:45.702 --> 20:47.621
- Put up what we talked about earlier.
- Yes, sir.

20:49.289 --> 20:52.459
She was wearing earrings
and was using her phone at work?

20:53.418 --> 20:54.962
Which store does she work at?

20:57.172 --> 21:00.926
The subway seems to be running
close to the store.

21:01.593 --> 21:03.011
It must be the Sillim-dong store.

21:03.136 --> 21:04.513
It's the one in Gasan-dong.

21:05.639 --> 21:07.391
I'm pretty sure it's Sillim-dong.

21:07.474 --> 21:09.184
Who's the supervisor in charge?

21:10.560 --> 21:11.853
That would be me.

21:12.771 --> 21:14.982
I'm sorry, sir. I'll rectify her mistakes.

21:15.065 --> 21:16.191
It's too late now.

21:17.317 --> 21:19.736
Do you not like your job?
If so, you can always quit.

21:21.446 --> 21:23.323
Mr. Jo.

21:23.782 --> 21:27.577
I used to supervise this store
before Ms. Kang took over.

21:28.161 --> 21:29.538
The owner there...

21:30.414 --> 21:32.165
I'm not sure if I should tell you this,

21:32.249 --> 21:33.792
but he's impossible to control.

21:33.917 --> 21:36.253
I remember having a hard time with him.

21:36.336 --> 21:38.588
I know Ms. Kang
gave them several warnings--

21:38.672 --> 21:40.632
Were they like that
since you were in charge?

21:40.882 --> 21:44.261
Then why wasn't it an issue back then?

21:54.271 --> 21:57.941
- Se-yeong, I was only trying to--
- Of course, you meant well.

21:58.525 --> 22:00.277
However, I can't thank you.

22:01.987 --> 22:03.572
I'll go to Gasan-dong store.

22:05.741 --> 22:07.868
I'm not suggesting you this
because I think I'm better.

22:08.368 --> 22:10.787
I've known the owner for a long time.
I know what to do.

22:11.872 --> 22:15.876
Also, you won't be able to work
with the mood you're currently in.

22:18.587 --> 22:20.881
I thought you might have
a harder time working today.

22:21.465 --> 22:22.424
Sorry?

22:25.469 --> 22:26.595
What does she mean?

22:40.650 --> 22:41.693
How scary.

22:42.903 --> 22:45.614
You keep doing a poor job
training your staff.

22:46.114 --> 22:49.076
Hair, earrings, rings, phone, and heels.

22:49.701 --> 22:53.455
You need to warn them
about the things they cannot do.

22:53.705 --> 22:55.373
Kids these days don't listen.

22:55.457 --> 22:57.709
I'm like a broken record.
I tell them over and over again--

22:57.793 --> 23:00.504
Don't take your anger out
on your hardworking employees

23:00.587 --> 23:02.547
by firing them. Okay?

23:04.341 --> 23:06.927
I won't give you a warning for this one.

23:07.010 --> 23:10.263
Thank you. We go way back, don't we?

23:10.555 --> 23:11.765
You mix your coffee, don't you?

23:12.265 --> 23:16.770
What? Why in the world would you say that?

23:17.145 --> 23:20.899
Your sales for the last four months
and the coffee supply don't match.

23:20.982 --> 23:24.694
You would need 10 bags of 500g,
which is 5kg per day.

23:24.778 --> 23:27.322
In a month, you would need at least 150kg.

23:27.781 --> 23:31.326
Last month, you ordered 135kg,
and 140kg the month before.

23:31.409 --> 23:33.495
This month, you only ordered 130kg.

23:34.371 --> 23:35.413
What's going on?

23:36.581 --> 23:39.376
How should I know?
It's what the cash register says.

23:39.459 --> 23:40.377
Should I pull a report?

23:40.919 --> 23:44.089
I'm reading from the copy
I got from the office.

23:44.297 --> 23:47.384
You know I'm good at
making your job easier.

23:48.426 --> 23:51.721
I don't know. The machine must be lying.

23:58.019 --> 24:01.523
"4 hot Americanos, 1 strawberry latte,
and 1 vanilla latte."

24:01.773 --> 24:04.359
- You didn't record this cash payment.
- Wait, that is...

24:04.484 --> 24:07.779
That's not it. We were so busy, and...

24:08.655 --> 24:11.575
Ms. Yoon!

24:13.785 --> 24:16.621
You have one more chance
until you strike out.

24:16.788 --> 24:19.374
As you know, the franchise agreement
can be terminated after that.

24:19.457 --> 24:23.044
What are you talking about?
I didn't do anything wrong.

24:24.421 --> 24:26.089
You won't be able to find anything.

24:29.843 --> 24:32.095
What's wrong with you?

24:33.096 --> 24:34.556
My goodness.

24:39.269 --> 24:41.730
Fine. I mixed other coffee, all right?

24:42.772 --> 24:45.650
Our sales were dropping,
and your coffee is so expensive.

24:45.859 --> 24:47.027
What else can I do?

24:47.694 --> 24:51.072
What kind of fool would run a business
that's going negative?

24:51.489 --> 24:53.325
You'll receive a mail
regarding this violation.

24:53.700 --> 24:55.660
- I'll deduct...
- Do what you want!

24:55.785 --> 24:59.748
Screw it! I'll burn it all down.

25:07.214 --> 25:11.593
Remind all the franchise owners
that there will be training next week.

25:12.093 --> 25:15.555
Can you print enough service manual
for the attendees

25:15.972 --> 25:18.016
and leave them on my desk
by the end of the day?

25:18.892 --> 25:20.560
Thank you, Ye-eun.

25:21.228 --> 25:24.689
Right. Make sure the font size
is large enough

25:24.773 --> 25:26.483
so that it is easier
for the owners to read.

25:27.484 --> 25:28.902
Okay. Bye.

26:00.433 --> 26:01.685
Yes, Mr. Choi.

26:02.894 --> 26:05.438
I just finished checking
the store in Gasan.

26:05.522 --> 26:06.773
I have a meeting

26:07.065 --> 26:09.901
with the owner of Pangyo store at 3 p.m.

26:11.861 --> 26:13.154
Bulgwang-dong, sir?

26:14.072 --> 26:15.031
Right now?

26:16.157 --> 26:20.036
Yes, it's not that far away.
I'll head over there right now.

26:21.329 --> 26:22.580
Gosh.

26:58.867 --> 27:00.952
You're so cute. Hey, you.

27:53.963 --> 27:55.340
It is you.

27:56.383 --> 27:58.093
I thought I was mistaken.

27:58.259 --> 27:59.636
When did you come back?

28:01.596 --> 28:02.889
While you were sleeping.

28:04.641 --> 28:06.226
That mouth of yours.

28:09.145 --> 28:10.230
Get over here.

28:14.943 --> 28:15.819
Hey.

28:19.614 --> 28:20.865
What are you doing?

28:21.699 --> 28:22.909
Come here.

28:33.044 --> 28:34.295
Hold on.

28:35.338 --> 28:36.256
That was close.

28:39.676 --> 28:43.638
I could get you if I wanted to,
but I'll just be nice.

28:43.722 --> 28:44.556
Sure.

28:46.766 --> 28:48.685
Are you having fun teasing me?

29:22.927 --> 29:25.847
So, did you find anyone you like?

29:27.807 --> 29:30.310
Unfortunately, you're still number one.

29:31.895 --> 29:34.314
If you weren't Gyeong-seon's brother,

29:34.564 --> 29:36.816
I would have killed you already.

29:41.362 --> 29:42.405
That's nice.

29:44.324 --> 29:46.785
I thought you'd want pork belly with soju.

29:47.160 --> 29:50.330
My colleagues already gave me
a warm welcoming party.

29:52.165 --> 29:55.001
Will you no longer get appointed
to a branch abroad?

29:55.293 --> 29:57.712
Don't say that.

29:57.921 --> 30:00.757
We take turns going abroad,
so I'll get to go again.

30:00.840 --> 30:04.052
You were in the States for three years.
Is that not enough?

30:05.970 --> 30:09.182
To be honest, I'd live there if I could.

30:09.974 --> 30:12.352
I think Korea's too small for me.

30:14.187 --> 30:16.731
Look at yourself talking big.

30:18.066 --> 30:20.735
You'd better not say that to your sister.

30:20.944 --> 30:22.779
She only pretends to be cold-hearted.

30:23.363 --> 30:25.740
She actually cares a lot about you.

30:26.282 --> 30:28.284
She's been busy for months

30:28.368 --> 30:30.787
trying to find a place for you.

30:31.246 --> 30:32.789
Show your sister some love.

30:35.458 --> 30:37.001
I do care for her a lot.

30:39.337 --> 30:40.797
I haven't told her that I am back.

30:41.464 --> 30:42.966
Are you crazy?

30:45.301 --> 30:48.763
She'll make a fuss
and cook a feast to feed me.

30:49.722 --> 30:51.057
She's already busy enough.

30:52.934 --> 30:54.644
Look at you.

30:54.936 --> 30:57.021
It seems like only yesterday
you were a little baby.

30:57.105 --> 30:59.023
When did you grow up so much?

31:00.066 --> 31:02.944
And when did you become so old...

31:05.154 --> 31:06.281
Do you...

31:07.031 --> 31:08.324
want me to end your life?

31:11.327 --> 31:13.037
You haven't heard that in a while, right?

31:15.707 --> 31:16.875
Are you dating anyone?

31:20.086 --> 31:23.506
You know, I'm always dating someone.

31:26.968 --> 31:28.052
I heard you became konjac.

31:33.683 --> 31:34.517
What...

31:36.352 --> 31:37.478
What's wrong?

31:39.522 --> 31:41.441
I can't walk in these heels any longer.

31:54.495 --> 31:55.455
Goodness.

31:55.955 --> 31:56.998
Thanks.

31:57.457 --> 31:58.708
My gosh.

32:00.501 --> 32:02.003
I'll do it.

32:07.175 --> 32:09.427
Hop on if what you actually wanted
was for me to carry you.

32:10.553 --> 32:11.763
Don't get funny with me.

32:14.891 --> 32:16.351
Can't you wear sneakers to work?

32:16.976 --> 32:18.394
Well, I can if I want to.

32:18.645 --> 32:21.564
- But does your boss not like it?
- He doesn't make it obvious.

32:21.814 --> 32:23.858
But I do need to be in heels sometimes.

32:24.525 --> 32:26.152
So you choose to be obedient.

32:27.320 --> 32:29.447
Let's just say I'm a professional.

32:30.281 --> 32:32.075
A true professional breaks taboos.

32:33.159 --> 32:34.869
Are you trying to teach me?

32:36.287 --> 32:38.247
- Should I begin?
- What?

32:39.958 --> 32:41.042
Where are you going?

32:42.418 --> 32:43.586
Where are you taking me?

32:44.420 --> 32:47.173
Hey, where are we...

33:12.156 --> 33:13.157
Hey.

33:29.465 --> 33:30.550
Be careful.

33:39.475 --> 33:42.270
What is this place?
Even I didn't know of this place.

33:42.895 --> 33:44.897
The administration center
is right around the corner.

33:45.064 --> 33:46.607
Your place is right across from there.

33:47.358 --> 33:49.444
I didn't know there was a shortcut.

33:49.944 --> 33:52.071
- How do you know this route?
- This route?

33:53.656 --> 33:56.534
You just saw them. I discovered it
while searching for a place to make out.

33:56.909 --> 33:59.120
My gosh.

34:00.538 --> 34:02.957
I taught Seung-ho how to smoke
when he was in 11th grade.

34:03.541 --> 34:06.711
He started smoking since 11th grade?
He was a nerd.

34:07.420 --> 34:10.882
That nerd probably had
his first kiss here with the girl

34:10.965 --> 34:12.425
he dated before college.

34:12.925 --> 34:13.968
My gosh.

34:15.636 --> 34:17.138
I'm going to tell Mom.

34:17.805 --> 34:19.682
You're too old to act naive.

34:20.349 --> 34:22.393
You really deserve a beating today.

34:25.563 --> 34:26.689
Stop right there.

34:34.989 --> 34:37.658
You became a lot smoother
than the last time I saw you.

34:47.710 --> 34:50.004
Our office moved while I was away.

34:50.171 --> 34:52.507
I have no idea what's around anymore.

34:53.883 --> 34:56.552
Can you give me a tour
of good restaurants during lunch?

34:57.220 --> 35:00.473
That's not hard to do,
but it'll be hard to find the time.

35:00.556 --> 35:01.641
I'm offsite a lot.

35:02.642 --> 35:05.103
Is this an excuse to get yourself out
of treating me?

35:05.478 --> 35:06.479
How did you know?

35:07.146 --> 35:10.108
Keep on asking me. If our times match,

35:10.191 --> 35:11.901
I'll buy you anything you want to eat.

35:24.413 --> 35:25.414
Bye.

35:53.359 --> 35:55.486
They are from a department store.
Did you buy something?

35:55.570 --> 35:57.113
- Nothing.
- Let me see.

35:57.196 --> 35:59.323
These are not mine.
I'm doing someone a favor.

36:00.324 --> 36:02.451
You reek of alcohol. Did you drink again?

36:02.535 --> 36:04.370
Gyu-min really needs to get a scolding.

36:04.537 --> 36:05.955
I saw someone else.

36:06.372 --> 36:10.376
I see. What does he want to eat?
I should buy groceries.

36:11.335 --> 36:12.378
I forgot.

36:12.587 --> 36:14.046
You haven't asked him yet?

36:14.338 --> 36:16.716
I've been busy. I'll ask him, okay?

36:17.675 --> 36:21.304
You shouldn't act so cranky
when you're with Gyu-min.

36:21.387 --> 36:23.139
You guys are getting old.

36:23.222 --> 36:26.559
You need to learn to compromise a little
in order to marry him.

36:26.642 --> 36:27.768
What marriage?

36:32.148 --> 36:34.609
It's not like we ever talked about it.

36:34.775 --> 36:38.154
That's why you should start talking.

36:38.321 --> 36:42.533
It's not easy to find
a good catch like Gyu-min.

36:42.700 --> 36:44.702
His mom, dad, and even his big brother

36:44.785 --> 36:46.829
are all alumni
of Seoul National University.

36:47.079 --> 36:50.374
- That's not all. What a great background.
- I got it.

36:51.292 --> 36:53.169
Why are you trying
to avoid the conversation?

36:53.252 --> 36:55.588
Do you know what it's like
whenever I see my friends?

36:55.671 --> 36:59.383
All of them get so jealous.
They make such a fuss about it.

36:59.467 --> 37:02.428
They tell me I'm so lucky.

37:02.511 --> 37:05.556
Not only are you marrying a lawyer,
I'll be getting a doctor,

37:05.640 --> 37:07.808
a judge, and a police commissioner
as my in-laws.

37:08.059 --> 37:10.519
They all have jobs
everyone would be jealous of.

37:10.645 --> 37:12.521
They say I can't ask for anything more.

37:12.647 --> 37:15.107
They go on and on about it.

37:16.359 --> 37:19.528
Your dad doesn't say it out loud,

37:19.612 --> 37:20.655
- but he--
- Mom.

37:20.738 --> 37:24.659
I'm really tired right now.
I want to shower and go to bed.

37:25.326 --> 37:27.370
You always say you're tired.

37:28.204 --> 37:29.664
Anyway, watch yourself.

37:38.506 --> 37:39.507
We're closed...

37:43.261 --> 37:45.721
You punk! I'm going to kill you!

37:47.181 --> 37:48.182
Hey!

37:50.059 --> 37:51.811
- Come here.
- Calm down!

37:54.522 --> 37:55.564
Come here.

37:56.274 --> 37:57.275
Come here.

38:05.366 --> 38:06.367
Let's go eat.

38:06.617 --> 38:08.369
I'm sorry. I'm meeting someone.

38:08.619 --> 38:10.538
My friend is waiting for me. Enjoy.

38:11.747 --> 38:12.832
Ms. Yoon, let's go.

38:13.082 --> 38:14.834
It's not like you still have a boyfriend.

38:16.794 --> 38:18.212
Hurry up. Come on.

38:25.303 --> 38:26.470
Ms. Yoon.

38:27.805 --> 38:31.475
I'm not okay, but I'll act like I am.
Let's go.

38:40.735 --> 38:42.486
Jin-a, buy me lunch.

38:45.781 --> 38:46.866
How about something spicy?

38:47.575 --> 38:49.952
- How about Jjamppong?
- No, something else.

38:50.119 --> 38:51.245
I have no appetite.

38:54.707 --> 38:55.833
Hello.

39:02.715 --> 39:05.259
Ms. Yoon, how about Chinese?

39:05.551 --> 39:07.136
I'm good with anything.

39:08.679 --> 39:10.681
Dong-u, what do you want?
I'll get jajangmyeon.

39:10.765 --> 39:11.766
I'll get the same.

39:14.268 --> 39:15.770
I see that your taste has gotten old.

39:17.229 --> 39:18.064
Shut it.

39:28.783 --> 39:30.326
More kimchi, please.

39:36.457 --> 39:38.834
I like it when we order different things.

39:39.502 --> 39:41.712
You can try a variety of dishes at once.

39:54.600 --> 39:55.601
Ms. Yoon.

39:56.769 --> 39:58.229
You are not that young anymore.

39:58.396 --> 40:00.356
You should date someone long-term
and get married.

40:00.439 --> 40:01.774
It's time for you to settle down.

40:10.658 --> 40:11.617
Give me a spoon of that.

40:13.077 --> 40:13.994
Sure.

40:15.871 --> 40:17.581
I say this because I worry about you.

40:18.541 --> 40:22.002
Nowadays, some people say being single
is better than being married.

40:22.336 --> 40:24.755
It wasn't easy in my days either.
It's all the same.

41:03.043 --> 41:04.628
- Are you up already?
- Yes.

41:05.588 --> 41:07.298
It must be a habit.

41:07.381 --> 41:09.592
My eyes just open up
when it's time for work.

41:10.426 --> 41:12.928
Lend me your car.
I have to go straight to a store.

41:13.012 --> 41:14.638
Sure, you know where the key is.

41:14.763 --> 41:16.432
The second shelf near the door.

41:16.515 --> 41:17.641
I know.

41:17.725 --> 41:19.310
It's still dark out. Drive carefully.

41:19.477 --> 41:20.728
Okay.

41:22.021 --> 41:23.481
You should go back to bed.

41:23.564 --> 41:24.648
No, thanks.

41:26.817 --> 41:28.819
- See you later.
- Be careful.

41:29.028 --> 41:30.029
Okay.

41:31.655 --> 41:34.116
Wipe the poster before putting it up.

41:34.200 --> 41:35.367
- Yes, ma'am.
- Will do.

41:38.621 --> 41:41.123
We won't open the machines
until the day before the opening.

41:41.290 --> 41:42.875
- Don't take the plastics off.
- Yes, ma'am.

41:46.253 --> 41:47.546
These boxes...

41:57.431 --> 42:00.684
Wow, Lee Gyu-min...
He was being a two-timer.

42:11.320 --> 42:14.198
WITH MY CUTIE-PIE.
HAD A GREAT TIME AT AN AWESOME RESORT.

42:24.583 --> 42:25.626
What is this?

42:25.876 --> 42:28.879
What do you think?
It's the true face of Gyu-min.

42:29.046 --> 42:32.883
I was dying to know
why he broke up with you,

42:32.967 --> 42:37.471
so I kept searching on Instagram
and finally found his girlfriend.

42:37.763 --> 42:40.808
Aren't those places
where you asked him to take you?

42:41.433 --> 42:45.521
Lee Gyu-min is such an asshole.
Was he always like this?

43:04.123 --> 43:06.709
MY LOVELY BOYFRIEND

43:11.839 --> 43:16.510
HE NEVER CEASES TO AMAZE ME.
I LOVE HIM SO MUCH.

43:23.934 --> 43:28.689
DATE NIGHT AT A WINE BAR.
UPLOADED ONE MINUTE AGO

44:02.139 --> 44:06.644
Could you give me the key to 3745?
I have to get something from the car.

44:06.727 --> 44:08.604
- Number 3745?
- Yes.

45:00.823 --> 45:01.865
What's wrong?

45:02.866 --> 45:04.701
I think I'm drunk.

45:06.703 --> 45:08.580
I think I'm drunk.

45:09.873 --> 45:12.209
- Are you tired?
- I can't...

45:12.835 --> 45:14.920
- I can't walk.
- Poor baby.

45:15.003 --> 45:17.631
Let's go home.
I'll massage your legs for you.

45:17.714 --> 45:19.049
Let's go.

45:19.258 --> 45:20.801
Watch your step.

45:21.051 --> 45:23.137
I can't... I can't walk.

45:23.303 --> 45:25.305
I'll go get my car. Wait here.

45:27.599 --> 45:29.643
- It's 3745.
- All right.

45:30.894 --> 45:32.688
- Was it 3745?
- Yes.

45:36.692 --> 45:37.526
How much is it?

46:19.943 --> 46:21.153
Let's go home now.

46:25.073 --> 46:26.200
What's this?

46:27.826 --> 46:29.369
- What?
- Are you two-timing me?

46:30.871 --> 46:32.331
What's that?

46:35.167 --> 46:36.710
What is that?

46:36.835 --> 46:39.713
How would I know, you fucking asshole?

46:39.922 --> 46:43.342
Ga-young,
how can you talk to me like that?

46:43.717 --> 46:45.385
Respect doesn't come with age.

46:46.136 --> 46:49.973
I normally don't even consider
going out with losers like you.

46:50.140 --> 46:53.685
I only went out on a few dates with you
because you wouldn't stop bothering me.

46:54.061 --> 46:55.187
Do you understand?

46:55.812 --> 46:57.814
Gosh, what a lousy day.

46:58.357 --> 47:01.443
- Hey.
- Don't you dare touch me!

47:02.778 --> 47:05.239
- Is this who you really are?
- My gosh.

47:06.990 --> 47:10.661
This may be who I really am,
but at least I never two-time someone.

47:10.744 --> 47:14.081
My goodness.
You should be ashamed of yourself.

47:14.289 --> 47:18.043
You were coming on to me so hard
just because I am young.

47:18.126 --> 47:20.003
You'd better stop talking to me that way.

47:20.087 --> 47:22.005
Do you want me to go on?

47:22.172 --> 47:23.632
I can keep cussing if I want to.

47:25.384 --> 47:27.553
I know you're young,
but you should know better.

47:27.636 --> 47:30.013
Don't you dare try to teach me.

47:31.014 --> 47:32.266
What a joke.

47:33.433 --> 47:34.351
What?

47:36.979 --> 47:38.730
Don't ever come near me again.

47:38.814 --> 47:41.275
If you do, I'm going to tell everyone
at your office about this.

47:44.027 --> 47:44.945
I can't believe this.

48:00.085 --> 48:01.795
Drink slowly.

48:02.254 --> 48:04.256
You're going to become a handful again.

48:05.132 --> 48:07.759
Just let me do what I want.

48:08.302 --> 48:10.887
You brat. I'm not your husband.

48:12.139 --> 48:15.767
I'd love it if you were my husband.

48:20.147 --> 48:21.773
I know it wasn't enough,

48:21.940 --> 48:24.985
but you still got your revenge.
Why are you still so down?

48:29.740 --> 48:31.074
I guess you were right.

48:32.409 --> 48:36.288
I guess I really don't have
good standards for men.

48:38.165 --> 48:40.500
On my way here, something came to my mind.

48:41.793 --> 48:44.379
All the guys I've dated until now...

48:45.797 --> 48:48.050
I sound as if I've dated a lot of guys.

48:48.467 --> 48:49.760
Anyway...

48:51.386 --> 48:56.433
All those moments that I thought were love

48:57.976 --> 49:01.229
might not have actually been true love.

49:03.190 --> 49:05.108
What is true love?

49:08.070 --> 49:11.073
I don't know.
I've never truly been in love.

49:13.492 --> 49:15.077
You're right.

49:18.872 --> 49:19.706
Hey.

49:21.458 --> 49:25.379
Knowing your own future
is a very sad thing.

49:27.130 --> 49:28.674
You should become a fortune-teller.

49:28.757 --> 49:29.716
What's your future like?

49:32.260 --> 49:35.764
I'll just live the way I've always lived.

49:36.306 --> 49:40.227
Then, I'll meet an average guy,

49:41.019 --> 49:42.813
get married, have children,

49:42.896 --> 49:44.439
and live the rest of my life with him.

49:44.606 --> 49:46.775
Oh, that kind of future.

49:48.276 --> 49:50.862
But I'm sure you can still be happy...

49:53.990 --> 49:55.117
with that kind of life.

49:58.078 --> 50:02.666
- Yes, I'm sure.
- Yes.

50:06.336 --> 50:08.046
You guys both look so sad.

50:08.922 --> 50:11.341
- Why did she drink so much?
- Hey.

50:11.425 --> 50:13.427
You wanted to go home together,
but you're drinking.

50:13.927 --> 50:15.220
This is our only happiness.

50:15.303 --> 50:17.305
That's because this is all you do.

50:17.389 --> 50:18.890
- You aren't dating--
- No.

50:25.063 --> 50:26.064
By the way,

50:26.898 --> 50:29.776
you seem drunker today than usual.

50:35.657 --> 50:37.200
She's sensitive.

50:37.284 --> 50:39.286
Why? Did someone call her konjac again?

50:41.246 --> 50:42.664
I'm going to go to the bathroom.

50:46.668 --> 50:50.297
- You think it's funny, don't you?
- Why are you...

50:50.422 --> 50:52.382
- You punk.
- Wait.

50:53.592 --> 50:55.844
I don't even have the energy to hit you.

50:56.470 --> 50:57.554
My arm hurts.

50:57.637 --> 50:59.765
That's so sad, Jin-a.

51:01.266 --> 51:02.684
What's sad?

51:02.768 --> 51:05.479
- Thank you.
- Sure.

51:05.562 --> 51:07.314
Okay, I got it.

51:07.397 --> 51:09.691
- Thank you, Gyeong-seon.
- My gosh.

51:09.816 --> 51:13.570
Don't think about anything,
and go to bed as soon as you get home.

51:13.653 --> 51:15.155
- Okay.
- Sleep tight.

51:15.238 --> 51:16.656
- Okay, Mom.
- Okay.

51:18.241 --> 51:20.452
Good girl. Get in the car.

51:20.535 --> 51:21.912
- Let's get you home.
- Okay.

51:21.995 --> 51:23.371
There you go. Let's go.

51:23.455 --> 51:25.457
- Am I going home alone?
- Yes. Watch your head.

51:25.540 --> 51:26.583
- Okay.
- Be careful.

51:26.666 --> 51:28.251
- Bye.
- Get in.

51:28.376 --> 51:29.920
- Bye.
- Take your purse.

51:30.003 --> 51:31.922
- Good. Have a safe ride home.
- Bye.

51:32.005 --> 51:34.132
Bye. Put your hand inside.

51:34.508 --> 51:35.592
My gosh.

51:36.676 --> 51:38.303
You guys really might get married.

51:39.095 --> 51:40.680
You'll have a pretty brother-in-law.

51:41.431 --> 51:42.641
- Take her home.
- Wait.

51:42.724 --> 51:45.143
- Bye.
- Who's going to pay me?

51:45.685 --> 51:47.145
Do you want a beating?

51:48.146 --> 51:50.106
You guys are so violent.

51:55.111 --> 51:57.906
Hey, she drank a lot.

51:58.490 --> 52:00.951
Don't go too fast. She drank a lot.

52:01.034 --> 52:02.327
- Okay.
- Bye.

52:02.410 --> 52:04.538
- Bye.
- See you.

52:06.540 --> 52:09.209
- Bye. See you. Put your seatbelt on.
- Okay.

52:10.168 --> 52:12.254
- Drive safely.
- Okay, Mom.

52:12.504 --> 52:14.089
No, I don't like that.

52:14.297 --> 52:15.340
Get going.

54:42.237 --> 54:43.530
Why did we stop?

54:51.413 --> 54:52.539
Let's go.

55:30.618 --> 55:32.787
- Did you just take a photo of me?
- No.

55:34.581 --> 55:35.623
Give me your phone.

55:36.458 --> 55:37.834
What do you want my phone for?

55:38.251 --> 55:39.961
Give it to me before I beat you up.

55:40.336 --> 55:41.963
Did you use to be a bully?

55:42.213 --> 55:44.924
Stop joking and give me your phone.
I know you took a photo.

55:45.216 --> 55:47.886
Why would I take a photo of you drooling?

55:52.515 --> 55:54.601
Stop lying. I don't drool.

55:59.439 --> 56:00.732
If you upload that photo,

56:00.815 --> 56:03.693
you'll go to jail for defamation
and violating my right of publicity.

56:04.277 --> 56:06.696
My gosh,
no one will be interested in it anyway.

56:06.780 --> 56:08.490
You must think you're really pretty.

56:09.365 --> 56:12.619
You'd better start treating me
with respect since I'm older.

56:15.288 --> 56:17.373
I keep using my age
to my benefit, don't I?

56:18.208 --> 56:19.292
I'm glad you know.

56:19.918 --> 56:22.587
I can only act this way around you.

56:24.631 --> 56:25.673
Thanks for today.

56:26.549 --> 56:29.552
I'll treat you to a meal
when I have time. See you.

56:43.650 --> 56:44.651
Bye.

57:18.935 --> 57:20.562
What are you talking about?

57:21.563 --> 57:23.690
Check if the Marketing Team
sent the product,

57:23.773 --> 57:26.818
and ask them when it'll arrive.
Call me after you check with them.

57:27.485 --> 57:29.487
Ms. Yoon, what's going on?

57:29.779 --> 57:32.407
People are lined up
because of the opening event.

57:32.490 --> 57:35.702
But we don't have the product.
How can this be?

57:36.035 --> 57:38.705
Mr. Jo told me that--

57:38.788 --> 57:40.748
I think there was a misunderstanding.

57:40.832 --> 57:42.834
I'll make sure everything goes smoothly.

57:42.917 --> 57:45.837
I'll also make sure
Mr. Jo hears about this.

57:45.920 --> 57:47.505
I'm really sorry, ma'am.

57:51.634 --> 57:52.760
What's taking so long?

57:54.345 --> 57:55.472
What happened?

57:58.683 --> 58:00.268
It didn't get approved?

58:01.603 --> 58:02.770
What do you mean?

58:02.854 --> 58:04.314
Mr. Oh,

58:05.523 --> 58:07.525
the free gifts we were meant to hand out

58:07.734 --> 58:10.028
at the opening event
didn't get delivered yet.

58:10.361 --> 58:12.822
I already told you that I placed an order.

58:19.078 --> 58:21.789
- Ma'am.
- My gosh.

58:22.040 --> 58:23.958
Stop making me repeat myself.

58:28.922 --> 58:29.756
You can go.

58:29.839 --> 58:30.965
Pardon?

58:31.799 --> 58:33.468
Go do your work. I'll take care of it.

58:34.093 --> 58:36.763
Ms. Yoon is currently at the store...

58:45.355 --> 58:47.607
Hello, this is Jeong Yeong-in.

58:49.484 --> 58:52.862
I called to ask you
for an urgent delivery.

58:54.447 --> 58:57.408
If it was something urgent,

58:58.326 --> 59:00.954
you could've given it to me separately.

59:01.788 --> 59:03.915
I have so many documents to sign.

59:04.499 --> 59:06.042
How am I...

59:06.793 --> 59:08.920
supposed to know what to...

59:09.587 --> 59:13.049
It was the file that had a yellow note
on the cover.

59:13.716 --> 59:15.593
I don't care. I never saw it.

59:16.719 --> 59:19.556
Noted, sir. I must have been mistaken.

59:19.639 --> 59:22.141
I'm sorry. I'll go now.

59:36.906 --> 59:37.991
URGENT APPROVAL NEEDED

01:00:01.931 --> 01:00:03.808
I'm so sorry.

01:00:03.891 --> 01:00:07.020
I'll deliver the gift
to every single person here.

01:00:07.604 --> 01:00:10.523
And you'll also receive a mobile coupon
redeemable for a cup of coffee.

01:00:10.607 --> 01:00:13.943
It'll be valid in all our stores
throughout the country.

01:00:14.485 --> 01:00:16.237
Again, I'm very sorry.

01:00:16.946 --> 01:00:17.905
I'm sorry.

01:00:20.533 --> 01:00:23.244
Apparently, Ms. Jeong in the Marketing
Team had signed the order form.

01:00:24.662 --> 01:00:25.705
I'm sorry.

01:00:26.664 --> 01:00:27.957
You should be sorry.

01:00:28.291 --> 01:00:30.835
Did you forget about it
or forget to check again?

01:00:32.670 --> 01:00:33.921
I forgot to check again.

01:00:34.756 --> 01:00:37.216
- That day, I told you to--
- Mr. Jo wants to see you.

01:00:39.135 --> 01:00:40.762
Make sure he doesn't run away.

01:00:40.845 --> 01:00:42.805
I'm going to beat the soul out of him.

01:00:50.021 --> 01:00:53.066
I told the other employees
to think of Jin-a as a role model.

01:00:53.775 --> 01:00:56.569
And I promised
to take good care of that store

01:00:56.653 --> 01:00:58.112
since it's owned by my family member.

01:00:58.655 --> 01:00:59.906
I became a liar.

01:01:01.199 --> 01:01:02.200
I'm sorry, sir.

01:01:04.285 --> 01:01:06.287
So you did not receive
anything that needed approval?

01:01:08.247 --> 01:01:12.126
That's what I was told,
so I'm guessing that's what...

01:01:18.174 --> 01:01:20.176
You need to clean up the mess you made.

01:01:21.552 --> 01:01:24.597
Yes. I'll send the products
to the customers.

01:01:24.722 --> 01:01:27.558
I'll also compensate them
with mobile coffee coupons.

01:01:28.685 --> 01:01:29.769
Is that all?

01:01:33.606 --> 01:01:37.110
I'll pay for everything myself
since it was my mistake.

01:01:39.237 --> 01:01:40.822
You know you can do better.

01:01:41.781 --> 01:01:43.157
Okay, you can go now.

01:01:54.836 --> 01:01:58.172
I should lay off some people.
They're all so laid back these days.

01:02:05.471 --> 01:02:06.472
Do you want one?

01:02:08.725 --> 01:02:11.269
Thanks for asking.
I already feel better now.

01:02:15.648 --> 01:02:16.816
You need 100, right?

01:02:17.024 --> 01:02:19.652
I placed an order
and told them it was urgent.

01:02:20.236 --> 01:02:22.822
Ms. Jeong, when did you...

01:02:25.158 --> 01:02:26.367
Thank you.

01:02:27.660 --> 01:02:29.287
Being cheerful suits you better.

01:02:41.090 --> 01:02:44.218
CREDIT CARD PAYMENT IS DUE ON JANUARY 25.
YOUR DUE BALANCE IS 211,690 WON.

01:02:45.511 --> 01:02:47.638
Perfect timing.

01:02:52.435 --> 01:02:53.436
Hey, Ye-eun.

01:02:54.812 --> 01:02:57.607
Ms. Yoon, where are you? It's lunchtime.

01:02:59.317 --> 01:03:00.651
I have a plan.

01:03:01.736 --> 01:03:04.781
Really? Because if you don't, you can--

01:03:04.864 --> 01:03:06.824
Why don't you believe me?

01:03:07.325 --> 01:03:10.870
Go eat with Dong-u. Don't worry about me.

01:03:11.162 --> 01:03:12.789
He's probably crying somewhere.

01:03:13.039 --> 01:03:16.083
Okay. Don't skip your meal, Ms. Yoon.

01:03:16.709 --> 01:03:17.752
Okay.

01:03:32.892 --> 01:03:34.310
Do you want to eat together?

01:03:36.229 --> 01:03:37.271
Hey.

01:03:39.315 --> 01:03:41.025
Do you want to play pool and bet on lunch?

01:03:41.192 --> 01:03:42.777
I have a plan.

01:03:42.985 --> 01:03:44.862
Stop lying. You have no friends.

01:03:45.738 --> 01:03:48.115
That's why I have a lot of girls.

01:03:51.410 --> 01:03:53.287
What? Were you serious?

01:04:20.773 --> 01:04:22.108
This place is nice.

01:04:25.278 --> 01:04:28.698
You would've been disappointed
if I chose the restaurant.

01:04:29.740 --> 01:04:31.075
Where do you usually go for lunch?

01:04:32.326 --> 01:04:35.162
I don't want to ruin this moment
by reminding myself of that.

01:04:39.250 --> 01:04:40.543
Do you want some wine?

01:04:41.335 --> 01:04:43.254
What? I'm working.

01:04:43.337 --> 01:04:44.964
You must break taboos
to be a professional.

01:04:46.757 --> 01:04:48.175
Seriously?

01:04:49.552 --> 01:04:51.929
- What are your house wines?
- Our house wines?

01:04:52.013 --> 01:04:53.890
- Could you bring us the menu?
- Sure.

01:05:05.067 --> 01:05:06.819
Could I pay...

01:05:06.903 --> 01:05:08.487
Your company already paid.

01:05:10.990 --> 01:05:13.034
Why did you get the bill?

01:05:13.117 --> 01:05:15.953
Gyeong-seon will scold me
for making you pay.

01:05:16.412 --> 01:05:18.456
Then you can pay for my lunch from now on.

01:05:19.123 --> 01:05:22.001
Fine. Anyway, thanks to you,

01:05:22.084 --> 01:05:24.795
I enjoyed a delicious meal.
I even broke a taboo.

01:05:26.505 --> 01:05:29.091
Now that you know what it's like
to break taboos, you're in trouble.

01:05:38.225 --> 01:05:40.269
- I had too much to eat.
- Twelfth floor.

01:05:40.853 --> 01:05:42.271
Seventeenth floor.

01:05:46.400 --> 01:05:48.444
Mr. Nam, are you coming back from lunch?

01:05:49.153 --> 01:05:50.154
Yes.

01:05:52.907 --> 01:05:54.408
Eighteenth floor.

01:05:59.038 --> 01:06:00.373
Regarding the delivery incident...

01:06:00.873 --> 01:06:02.833
You have to do things in advance.

01:06:03.501 --> 01:06:04.919
You're usually good. What happened?

01:06:05.252 --> 01:06:06.420
I'm sorry, sir.

01:06:06.837 --> 01:06:08.839
It won't happen again.

01:06:10.132 --> 01:06:14.428
Do we have last month's sales report
from all the stores?

01:06:15.346 --> 01:06:17.556
- Is it not ready yet?
- I already...

01:06:19.600 --> 01:06:20.935
I'll find it for you, sir.

01:06:22.770 --> 01:06:24.647
Twelfth floor. Canceled.

01:06:33.030 --> 01:06:34.156
Cheer up.

01:06:37.326 --> 01:06:39.412
Yoon Jin-a, you'd better keep your head.

01:06:39.495 --> 01:06:41.122
I won't let this happen.

01:06:41.580 --> 01:06:43.207
You say your future is predictable,

01:06:43.290 --> 01:06:45.876
but you cannot date someone
like Lee Gyu-min again.

01:06:46.293 --> 01:06:48.170
You have to create your own fate.

01:06:48.546 --> 01:06:51.841
You can change your life
depending on what you do.

01:06:51.924 --> 01:06:53.342
Don't do anything stupid, all right?

01:06:54.135 --> 01:06:56.345
I don't want to watch you suffer anymore,
okay?

01:06:56.429 --> 01:06:59.181
I got it. Don't worry.

01:06:59.557 --> 01:07:02.268
- I'll call you later. Okay.
- I'll be going home.

01:07:02.351 --> 01:07:03.352
Bye.

01:07:04.145 --> 01:07:05.354
See you tomorrow.

01:07:17.575 --> 01:07:19.118
I'm leaving.

01:07:19.201 --> 01:07:21.162
- Bye.
- Bye.

01:07:39.930 --> 01:07:42.141
Why won't you reply to my texts
or pick up my calls?

01:07:43.017 --> 01:07:44.268
What is it that you have to say?

01:07:46.270 --> 01:07:48.606
This isn't the right place for it.
Let's go somewhere quiet.

01:07:48.689 --> 01:07:51.358
Forget it. Just say what you have to
right here right now.

01:08:33.317 --> 01:08:35.444
Come on, we shouldn't end it like this.
Let's go talk.

01:08:35.528 --> 01:08:37.279
- I said, do it here.
- Please--

01:08:38.989 --> 01:08:41.534
- Hey, what are you doing?
- Playing your boyfriend.

01:08:41.617 --> 01:08:43.452
Act natural. Smile.

01:08:43.536 --> 01:08:46.413
Wait. Who is he?

01:08:47.706 --> 01:08:48.666
Well...

01:08:49.208 --> 01:08:50.417
And who are you?

01:08:50.501 --> 01:08:51.836
I'm Jin-a's boyfriend.

01:08:53.045 --> 01:08:54.797
- Fuck off.
- What did you say?

01:08:55.548 --> 01:08:56.590
I said, fuck off.

01:08:56.674 --> 01:08:59.135
Are you her stalker? Should I report you?

01:08:59.385 --> 01:09:01.220
Jin-a, who is this guy?

01:09:04.974 --> 01:09:06.308
Is this the police?

01:09:06.642 --> 01:09:08.894
- I'm reporting a stalker.
- What are you doing?

01:09:08.978 --> 01:09:10.479
- Are you in trouble?
- Let's talk later.

01:09:10.563 --> 01:09:12.022
Are you insane?

01:09:12.106 --> 01:09:13.691
- Report what?
- I'll call you later.

01:09:16.694 --> 01:09:18.404
My sister is going to kill me.

01:09:19.989 --> 01:09:21.240
I'll explain it to her.

01:09:35.504 --> 01:09:37.006
Should I not have done that?

01:09:38.591 --> 01:09:39.675
No.

01:09:41.218 --> 01:09:43.137
Then why aren't you saying anything?

01:09:43.679 --> 01:09:45.055
You seem mad.

01:09:47.224 --> 01:09:48.559
I'm embarrassed.

01:09:49.643 --> 01:09:51.478
I must be a pathetic person

01:09:51.562 --> 01:09:53.314
to get the help of a friend's brother.

01:09:53.397 --> 01:09:55.441
What kind of ridiculous person
was I dating?

01:09:56.358 --> 01:09:57.776
It's so embarrassing.

01:09:59.653 --> 01:10:01.238
I'm not surprised at all.

01:10:01.572 --> 01:10:03.657
You have a bad taste in men.

01:10:04.992 --> 01:10:06.160
That's true.

01:10:08.704 --> 01:10:10.206
You were lucky.

01:10:10.497 --> 01:10:13.584
You could have ended up living
with that loser for the rest of your life.

01:10:13.667 --> 01:10:14.835
You're super lucky.

01:10:18.047 --> 01:10:20.132
You make it sound better.

01:10:30.517 --> 01:10:31.685
Hey, Jun-hui.

01:10:32.645 --> 01:10:33.479
What?

01:10:36.690 --> 01:10:39.985
You said you know someone
working for the coffee company

01:10:40.653 --> 01:10:42.029
in this building, right?

01:10:42.488 --> 01:10:43.364
Yes.

01:10:45.616 --> 01:10:46.909
Can you set me up with her?

01:10:50.746 --> 01:10:51.622
What...

01:10:52.456 --> 01:10:53.999
What's with those eyes?

01:10:54.625 --> 01:10:55.793
Can't I ask?

01:10:57.002 --> 01:10:57.920
Are you high?

01:10:58.003 --> 01:11:01.048
I'm just a handsome guy
asking to meet a beautiful girl.

01:11:03.759 --> 01:11:05.010
Are you into her?

01:11:05.928 --> 01:11:06.971
You're talking nonsense.

01:11:07.054 --> 01:11:09.890
If that's not it,
what is your fucking problem?

01:11:10.432 --> 01:11:13.686
To be honest, Kang Se-yeong
is the hottest person in this building.

01:11:14.561 --> 01:11:16.438
Am I not even allowed
to talk to her for once?

01:11:16.522 --> 01:11:17.439
Is that so?

01:11:18.065 --> 01:11:19.066
Who?

01:11:20.109 --> 01:11:21.610
Let's end the meeting here.

01:11:26.240 --> 01:11:28.575
I'll clean up. Make a round of calls
to the franchise owners.

01:11:28.659 --> 01:11:30.119
Yes, ma'am.

01:11:30.577 --> 01:11:31.662
I'll help.

01:11:34.123 --> 01:11:35.749
You don't have to be sorry.

01:11:35.833 --> 01:11:37.876
The rumors would have spread
at some point.

01:11:39.003 --> 01:11:41.714
I kind of know what you're talking about,

01:11:41.922 --> 01:11:43.924
but I don't know why I should be sorry.

01:11:45.759 --> 01:11:48.178
Then why are you acting strange?

01:11:48.262 --> 01:11:49.805
You would never do something like this.

01:11:51.098 --> 01:11:52.725
I have a question for you.

01:11:55.311 --> 01:11:57.855
A man came to your rescue

01:11:57.938 --> 01:11:59.481
when your ex came yesterday.

01:12:00.691 --> 01:12:01.734
Who is he?

01:12:03.068 --> 01:12:04.987
Like you said, he's my savior.

01:12:05.946 --> 01:12:07.072
Are you interested in him?

01:12:07.823 --> 01:12:08.741
What?

01:12:09.742 --> 01:12:11.368
Then it's okay for me
to hit on him, right?

01:12:14.038 --> 01:12:15.622
- Sure.
- He's single, right?

01:12:17.124 --> 01:12:20.753
I'm not sure. I don't know for sure.

01:12:21.128 --> 01:12:22.713
He has such high standards.

01:12:22.796 --> 01:12:25.424
There are a lot of pretty girls
around him--

01:12:25.507 --> 01:12:27.176
That means he's not taken.

01:12:27.718 --> 01:12:28.886
It's worth a shot.

01:12:33.349 --> 01:12:34.725
I'll get going then.

01:12:35.225 --> 01:12:36.310
I thought you were helping.

01:12:37.227 --> 01:12:38.562
I'll carry this for you.

01:12:44.109 --> 01:12:47.237
- Let's go! Cheers!
- Cheers!

01:13:21.730 --> 01:13:23.107
Here's the meat.

01:13:23.190 --> 01:13:25.317
Ms. Yoon, sit down.

01:13:27.319 --> 01:13:29.822
Come on. Have a drink.

01:13:33.575 --> 01:13:35.035
Should I get us more meat or alcohol?

01:13:35.744 --> 01:13:37.246
Just stay seated.

01:13:37.329 --> 01:13:38.997
But even Ms. Yoon is doing it.

01:13:42.000 --> 01:13:42.918
Raise your glasses.

01:13:45.129 --> 01:13:50.092
Here's to our future, our love,
and our career.

01:13:50.342 --> 01:13:51.593
Let them propel like a missile!

01:13:51.677 --> 01:13:53.303
- Missile!
- Missile!

01:13:55.264 --> 01:13:56.265
How about we do this?

01:13:56.890 --> 01:13:57.808
Sure.

01:14:07.943 --> 01:14:11.697
The thing is, we don't have any missiles.

01:14:21.707 --> 01:14:23.083
Jin-a sure is a tough cookie.

01:14:23.750 --> 01:14:25.002
I would never go near those men.

01:14:25.085 --> 01:14:27.754
That's why she is their favorite.

01:14:30.174 --> 01:14:31.842
They call her "Ms. Tambourine"
for a reason.

01:14:31.967 --> 01:14:35.095
I know you like her,
but don't take after that.

01:14:37.890 --> 01:14:38.849
Okay.

01:14:43.854 --> 01:14:45.856
Ms. Geum, how about a drink?

01:14:45.939 --> 01:14:47.024
I need to use the restroom.

01:14:47.524 --> 01:14:50.110
Wait for me. Excuse me.

01:14:51.028 --> 01:14:53.822
Ye-eun, have a drink. Come on.

01:14:54.823 --> 01:14:55.824
Relax.

01:14:59.161 --> 01:15:00.412
You can go with me.

01:15:00.704 --> 01:15:02.039
I have to go now.

01:15:02.247 --> 01:15:04.082
- Bye.
- See you at work.

01:15:04.166 --> 01:15:05.375
- Bye.
- Bye.

01:15:05.792 --> 01:15:07.127
I have to be somewhere.

01:15:07.252 --> 01:15:08.670
Can you tell them for me?

01:15:08.962 --> 01:15:09.796
Well...

01:15:11.340 --> 01:15:12.341
We should go too.

01:15:12.758 --> 01:15:14.760
He wouldn't like it if we all leave.

01:15:15.177 --> 01:15:17.846
He will start nagging
if I sit there sulking.

01:15:18.013 --> 01:15:20.891
- I'm leaving. Bye.
- But...

01:15:22.309 --> 01:15:24.144
Where did everyone...

01:15:24.228 --> 01:15:25.896
- Yoon Jin-a.
- My gosh!

01:15:26.480 --> 01:15:27.773
Come and sing a tune.

01:15:28.815 --> 01:15:31.360
I'm sorry, but I have to get back to work.

01:15:31.443 --> 01:15:33.946
You are single now. Don't back out.

01:15:34.279 --> 01:15:35.739
You can stay out until late.

01:15:37.783 --> 01:15:40.494
I didn't back out
even when I had a boyfriend.

01:15:41.078 --> 01:15:43.163
Today, I have some work left to do.

01:15:44.039 --> 01:15:45.457
- I have to go.
- Ms. Yoon...

01:15:48.752 --> 01:15:50.337
Did she just walk all over me?

01:15:51.088 --> 01:15:52.923
Sir, I think everybody else went inside.

01:16:13.860 --> 01:16:15.070
What are you still doing here?

01:16:15.904 --> 01:16:17.823
I was just leaving. And you?

01:16:18.323 --> 01:16:19.908
Did you come here for a second round?

01:16:20.909 --> 01:16:22.911
Yes, and for work.

01:16:23.412 --> 01:16:26.415
Are you going home or to Gyeong-seon?

01:16:26.999 --> 01:16:29.543
I don't have to worry about her.
I'm going to a club.

01:16:30.335 --> 01:16:31.336
A club?

01:16:34.089 --> 01:16:35.841
That must be fun.

01:16:36.925 --> 01:16:38.927
Are you going there to pick up girls?

01:16:39.928 --> 01:16:42.306
I already know enough girls, so no.

01:16:43.390 --> 01:16:44.308
One second.

01:16:45.851 --> 01:16:46.685
Hi, Se-mi.

01:16:48.812 --> 01:16:49.938
I'm at the office.

01:16:51.356 --> 01:16:53.775
Okay, I'll be there soon. I'm leaving now.

01:16:53.859 --> 01:16:55.027
- Okay.
- Bye, then.

01:17:04.953 --> 01:17:06.121
Ji-hye, hi.

01:17:07.164 --> 01:17:08.206
Where are you?

01:17:09.416 --> 01:17:10.876
Okay.

01:17:12.502 --> 01:17:13.337
See you soon.

01:20:31.701 --> 01:20:34.621
You have to meet someone new
to get over your ex-boyfriend.

01:20:35.247 --> 01:20:36.790
You should start seeing someone new.

01:20:37.123 --> 01:20:40.794
How much meaning should I put into
what a guy says or does to me?

01:20:40.877 --> 01:20:41.711
Pretty much none.

01:20:43.880 --> 01:20:48.051
Jin-a was always at the top of her game.
What's up with her lately?

01:20:48.552 --> 01:20:52.013
Mr. Kong doesn't know when to stop
because you don't tell him off.

01:20:52.097 --> 01:20:53.557
Anyone you're interested in?

01:20:54.182 --> 01:20:56.101
You do. How old is she?

01:20:56.184 --> 01:20:57.477
Is she 23 or 24?

01:20:57.561 --> 01:20:58.603
She's 35.

01:20:58.687 --> 01:20:59.813
How is that even possible?

01:21:01.273 --> 01:21:04.109
Are looks all that matter to guys?

01:21:05.277 --> 01:21:06.278
You're prettier.

01:21:07.737 --> 01:21:09.739
Subtitle translation by Choi Hyeon-ju
